name: NYDailyNews
text:
A voter registration form was sent to a long-dead Georgia cat named Cody.

“We’ve got them several times before, but we rip them, throw ‘em away,” owner Ron Tims said, adding the feline would have voted Democat.
https://t.co/pA00aVt9Wa

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Ex-US Gymnastics coach Terry Gray was arrested and is facing 14 felony counts on multiple charges of lewdness with a minor.

Gray coached the USA Gymnastics women’s national team prior to his suspension last October amid allegations of sexual misconduct.
https://t.co/EZwPZE0Y5l

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Still on the concussion list, Masahiro Tanaka is waiting out the tropical storm by playing catch in right field to stay sharp.

“Anytime we’re talking about a concussion, we’re making sure we’re moving slowly and smartly,” said Yankees manager Aaron Boone.
https://t.co/wIc6YvGSgj

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Aaron Judge was scratched from a Yankees' scrimmage with a stiff neck and isn't expected back until Sunday.

“Obviously didn’t want to force anything today, so hopefully he can be in there tomorrow,” manager Aaron Boone said.
https://t.co/8VjlJPCMSS

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Bollywood superstar Amitabh Bachchan tested positive for coronavirus.

Bachchan rose to stardom in the early 1970s and reached superstar status in the 1980s. He’s known as India’s “greatest living actor.”
https://t.co/sS8BStmW0w

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Aaron Hicks trusts video games will help the Yankees follow COVID-19 protocols.

“I’m not too worried about my team and you know, going out and getting wild, cuz they like their video games," Hicks said.

text:
An argument over whether Penny Hardaway is a good coach led to Tyrone Taylor, a Memphis man, punching his cousin in the face and then shooting him.

It was not clear whether Taylor was pro- or anti-Hardaway.
